	dprr:hasNoteText "Condemned in 74 for using his veto contrary to the Cornelian laws (Cic. Verr. 2.1.155-157; cf. Schol. Gron. 341 Stangl). Said to have supported Cotta's law regarding the tribunate (Ps.-Ascon. 255 Stangl; see above, Consuls)." .
